instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle follows the Model‑Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) abstraction hierarchy: (1) Requirements phase, (2) Functional architecture, (3) Logical architecture, and (4) Product/technical layer.  At each level, different modeling notations and tools are employed.  Requirements are typically captured in textual or diagrammatic form.  Functional architecture is expressed with SysML, notably SysML Interaction Block Diagrams (IBDs) for component structure and inter‑connectivity.  Logical architecture is described using Architecture Description Languages (ADLs) such as ACME, AADL, or MontiArc, which capture components, interfaces, and connectors from a component‑and‑connector perspective.  The product/technical layer is realized with code (e.g., C++ or Java) or simulation models (e.g., MathWorks Simulink).  The document emphasizes that these phases are complementary and that a comprehensive Digital Twin may integrate models across multiple notations, although explicit transition management and governance mechanisms are not detailed."
]

